Why Adaptive Software Maintenance Is Important
Adaptive maintenance focuses on modifying existing software to respond to environmental changes, such as updates in operating systems, new hardware deployments, or integration with other applications. By implementing adaptive maintenance, businesses can preserve functionality, ensure user satisfaction, and sustain optimal application performance.

